WEBVTT

00:05.273 --> 00:07.175
Last season on Bosch...

00:07.241 --> 00:09.043
Don't walk away from--

00:10.211 --> 00:11.512
- Oh!
- Hey! Hey!

00:11.579 --> 00:13.814
Hey, Harry.
How's it hanging?

00:13.881 --> 00:15.549
Welcome back, partner.

00:15.616 --> 00:17.885
A man named Anthony Allen was
murdered over the weekend.

00:17.951 --> 00:19.220
Ohh!

00:19.287 --> 00:20.521
His body was
discovered yesterday

00:20.588 --> 00:22.456
in the trunk of his car
above Mulholland.

00:22.523 --> 00:24.558
When you're finished here,
go notify the next of kin.

00:24.625 --> 00:26.294
- Do we know who that is yet?
- Veronica Allen.

00:26.360 --> 00:27.461
Well, do you have a suspect?

00:27.528 --> 00:29.130
We came up here
to talk to Carl Nash,

00:29.197 --> 00:30.531
but he's not
at work today.

00:30.598 --> 00:32.500
Why on earth would you
want to speak with him?

00:32.566 --> 00:34.835
He's become a person
of interest in this case.

00:34.902 --> 00:36.337
Not that you'd know this,

00:36.404 --> 00:38.272
but he's got
quite a checkered past.

00:40.841 --> 00:42.143
My lawyer called.

00:42.210 --> 00:44.212
Should be on the
probate docket any day.

00:44.278 --> 00:45.846
When exactly?

00:45.913 --> 00:48.749
Soon. Just be patient.

00:48.816 --> 00:50.751
Patience is my middle name.

00:50.818 --> 00:52.520
These cases
are 35 years old.

00:52.586 --> 00:55.423
Doesn't matter. A friend
of my mother's contacted me,

00:55.489 --> 00:57.891
told me my mother went there
the night she was murdered.

00:57.958 --> 00:59.493
This is new information.

00:59.560 --> 01:00.828
Who was he?

01:00.894 --> 01:02.530
He called himself Mitch.

01:02.596 --> 01:04.432
It's the only name
I ever knew him by.

01:04.498 --> 01:07.000
What about the detective?
Do you remember his name?

01:07.067 --> 01:08.936
- No, I--
- Was it Caffrey?

01:09.002 --> 01:10.138
John Caffrey?

01:10.204 --> 01:12.806
Fox Mitchell
was an alias, okay?

01:12.873 --> 01:14.375
He was a snitch.

01:14.442 --> 01:16.210
You didn't even talk
to him off book?

01:16.277 --> 01:18.579
I did the right thing.
I asked Narcotics

01:18.646 --> 01:20.714
to make him available
for questioning.

01:20.781 --> 01:22.216
That request was denied.

01:22.283 --> 01:24.385
So you just
laid down on it.

01:24.452 --> 01:26.854
So what's going on at home?

01:26.920 --> 01:28.156
I don't know.

01:28.222 --> 01:30.491
Mom and Reggie were
arguing a lot,

01:30.558 --> 01:32.893
and then all of a sudden
he goes to Hong Kong.

01:32.960 --> 01:34.662
There's been an
officer-involved shooting.

01:34.728 --> 01:37.731
I got a call to pick you up
and bring you to the scene.

01:44.638 --> 01:46.006
Oh, my boy.

01:46.073 --> 01:48.242
In memory of your son,

01:48.309 --> 01:50.678
and on behalf
of a grateful city

01:50.744 --> 01:53.714
and the Los Angeles
Police Department.

01:53.781 --> 01:58.219
You... killed him.

01:58.286 --> 02:01.021
I can't stand
to look at you.

02:01.088 --> 02:04.292
I agreed to accept the position
of Interim Chief of Police

02:04.358 --> 02:05.759
to honor my son

02:05.826 --> 02:08.896
and help lead the department
out of this current crisis.

02:08.962 --> 02:11.399
But I will not be accepting
the job permanently,

02:11.465 --> 02:13.301
no matter
who wins the election.

02:13.367 --> 02:15.002
You're just gonna walk away?

02:15.068 --> 02:17.004
I'm going to have
to ask you to leave.

02:17.070 --> 02:18.239
Not without
my fucking money.

02:18.306 --> 02:19.707
You know, I'm
calling the police.

02:19.773 --> 02:21.675
No, you are not!

02:21.742 --> 02:23.244
What happened?

02:23.311 --> 02:25.045
He attacked me.

02:25.112 --> 02:26.180
And how many times
did you hit him?

02:26.247 --> 02:27.981
Once or-- or twice.

02:28.048 --> 02:29.683
I don't--
I don't really remember.

02:29.750 --> 02:30.751
I was terrified.

02:30.818 --> 02:33.621
- You feared for your life.
- I did.

02:33.687 --> 02:36.257
So is that enough?

02:36.324 --> 02:38.392
- Bosch!
- I'm good!

02:45.566 --> 02:46.600
Aah!

02:49.102 --> 02:50.404
Shit.

02:55.108 --> 02:56.810
Arno Apperson,

02:56.877 --> 02:58.546
also known
as Fox Mitchell.

02:58.612 --> 03:01.682
These are names I haven't
heard in a long time.

03:01.749 --> 03:03.317
What are you
looking at him for?

03:03.384 --> 03:05.953
Murder of Marjorie Lowe,

03:06.019 --> 03:07.154
my mother.

03:07.221 --> 03:09.457
Jesus.

03:11.725 --> 03:13.661
You tied Apperson
to your mother's murder?

03:13.727 --> 03:15.496
No, he did it.
And this department,

03:15.563 --> 03:17.598
the D.A.'s office
protected him afterward,

03:17.665 --> 03:20.334
put him in
the Relocation Program.

03:20.401 --> 03:21.902
I want to know
where he is.

03:21.969 --> 03:24.071
I'll see what I
can find out.

03:24.137 --> 03:25.606
What's up, man?

03:25.673 --> 03:27.875
I'm looking for
Big Wave Dave. He around?

03:27.941 --> 03:29.843
He's been dead a while now.

03:29.910 --> 03:31.379
This him?

03:31.445 --> 03:33.981
Yeah. Dave Arenson.

04:33.941 --> 04:35.275
Shit.

06:06.767 --> 06:07.901
Fuck.

06:10.137 --> 06:11.605
Fuck.

06:19.413 --> 06:21.682
All right. All right.

06:29.289 --> 06:30.424
Shit.

06:42.436 --> 06:44.237
Returning
from the national picture,

06:44.304 --> 06:45.906
with 80% of the vote counted,

06:45.973 --> 06:48.842
incumbent mayor Hector Ramos
has an 11-point lead

06:48.909 --> 06:51.979
over Republican challenger
District Attorney Rick O'Shea.

06:52.045 --> 06:53.681
Some observers believe

06:53.747 --> 06:55.516
O'Shea's bid
for the city's top job

06:55.583 --> 06:57.417
was fatally damaged
a year ago

06:57.485 --> 06:58.919
by the video that showed him

06:58.986 --> 07:00.721
ordering
the shacklesremoved

07:00.788 --> 07:02.690
from a murder suspect
who then escaped custody,

07:02.756 --> 07:04.424
shooting a prosecutor

07:04.492 --> 07:05.993
and wounding
a police detective.

07:06.059 --> 07:07.928
There are still
two years remaining

07:07.995 --> 07:10.297
to O'Shea's term
as District Attorney,

07:10.363 --> 07:11.832
but the once rising star

07:11.899 --> 07:14.201
appears to be at
a crossroads in his career.

07:28.148 --> 07:29.449
Think you've had enough.

07:29.517 --> 07:31.018
Fuck you I've had enough.

07:31.084 --> 07:32.920
I'll tell you
when I've had enough.

07:32.986 --> 07:37.190
Got no call to cut me off
long as he's buying.

07:42.362 --> 07:44.064
Pour yourself one.

07:44.131 --> 07:46.700
It's on him.

07:46.767 --> 07:48.001
That okay with you?

07:48.068 --> 07:50.037
Why the fuck not?

07:52.139 --> 07:54.107
- There you go.
- That's good.

08:03.917 --> 08:06.820
From Atwater Village
to Arlington Heights,

08:06.887 --> 08:09.122
from Highland Park
to the Hollywood Hills,

08:09.189 --> 08:10.824
From Sylmar to South L.A.--

08:10.891 --> 08:12.693
...the people of Los Angeles

08:12.760 --> 08:15.729
have sent a message,
a strong message, that--

08:15.796 --> 08:18.365
- Bosch.
- This is Webster at Rampart.

08:18.431 --> 08:20.433
Sorry to bother you so late,

08:20.500 --> 08:22.736
but I got Ed Gunn here again.

08:22.803 --> 08:24.304
What do you want me
to do with him?

08:24.371 --> 08:25.639
Keep him awake
till I get there.

08:25.706 --> 08:26.907
I'm on my way.

08:28.375 --> 08:30.177
Conscious when I called you.

08:31.511 --> 08:32.913
I swear.

08:32.980 --> 08:35.448
- What's this mutt to you?
- Cold case.

08:35.515 --> 08:37.250
Serial killer.

08:37.317 --> 08:39.019
No shit.

08:39.086 --> 08:40.420
Him?

08:40.487 --> 08:42.856
Who'd he kill?
Some other rummies?

08:43.991 --> 08:46.059
Couple young women,
back in the day.

08:46.126 --> 08:47.394
Gonna book him?

08:47.460 --> 08:49.029
The sheriffs
don't want him.

08:49.096 --> 08:51.164
We'll frick him
in the morning,

08:51.231 --> 08:52.733
soon as he's sober.

08:52.800 --> 08:54.367
I'll be back
before that happens.

08:54.434 --> 08:55.703
I need a word.

10:40.908 --> 10:42.743
