Okay.

12:14.367 --> 12:15.235
Where are your keys?

12:15.302 --> 12:17.771
Wait a minute.
I got them.

12:17.838 --> 12:19.439
All right.

12:19.506 --> 12:20.941
Oh, you got 'em?

12:21.008 --> 12:22.175
Okay. Good. Come on.

12:22.242 --> 12:24.344
- Okay.
- Come on. Thank you.

13:30.243 --> 13:32.612
- Morning.
- Morning.

13:32.679 --> 13:33.813
Breakfast?

13:33.881 --> 13:34.948
I'll grab
something at school.

13:35.015 --> 13:36.249
You look nice.

13:37.417 --> 13:38.585
Thanks.

13:38.651 --> 13:39.752
I got court today.

13:39.819 --> 13:41.088
But tired.

13:41.154 --> 13:44.324
Up late
watching the returns.

13:46.026 --> 13:47.760
Presidential election?

13:47.827 --> 13:49.529
Dad, don't be a derp.

13:49.596 --> 13:52.465
I'm totally putting you on.
I even know who won.

13:52.532 --> 13:54.334
Uh-huh. I'm gonna
quiz you on that later.

13:54.401 --> 13:56.003
I'm gonna be able
to vote next year.

13:56.069 --> 13:58.071
Oof. That's
a terrifying thought.

13:58.138 --> 14:00.740
And when are you gonna
let me get my license?

14:00.807 --> 14:03.310
Hmm. Significantly
more terrifying thought.

14:03.376 --> 14:05.312
I have my permit.
You can teach me.

14:05.378 --> 14:08.681
Whoa. Hat trick.
You're on a roll.

14:08.748 --> 14:10.417
But you already testified.

14:10.483 --> 14:12.953
No, the defense lawyer
reserved their
cross examination

14:13.020 --> 14:14.454
until the end
of their case.

14:14.521 --> 14:16.823
- Do you think she'll get off?
- Might.

14:16.890 --> 14:18.225
Can't predict juries.

14:18.291 --> 14:19.859
And you're sure she did it?

14:20.994 --> 14:22.562
Beyond a reasonable doubt.

14:22.629 --> 14:23.863
You're gonna say that?

14:23.931 --> 14:25.465
I can only answer
the questions they ask me

14:25.532 --> 14:26.466
truthfully.

14:28.969 --> 14:30.737
- Uch.
- What?

14:30.803 --> 14:31.871
You were doing so well.

14:31.939 --> 14:34.374
I'm gonna quit again.

14:34.441 --> 14:36.809
I promise.

14:36.876 --> 14:38.011
Soon.

14:43.750 --> 14:45.485
I want you to see this.

14:47.955 --> 14:49.056
Okay?

14:49.122 --> 14:50.223
You shouldn't litter.

14:50.290 --> 14:51.858
You said
you wanted me to stop.

14:51.925 --> 14:53.660
I-- I just stopped.
You saw it.

14:53.726 --> 14:55.895
For real this time?
You promise?

14:57.931 --> 14:59.366
I promise.

14:59.432 --> 15:00.833
Truthfully?

15:00.900 --> 15:03.203
You really do
take after your mother.

15:18.051 --> 15:19.286
What the fuck?

15:20.820 --> 15:22.489
5:25 a.m. $500 bond.

15:22.555 --> 15:23.590
Who wrote the bond?

15:24.691 --> 15:25.792
AAA Bail.

15:25.858 --> 15:27.160
He was gonna
be released anyway.

15:27.227 --> 15:28.962
Who'd waste the money
to bail him out?

15:29.029 --> 15:30.897
- Family. Friend.
- He's got no friends.

15:30.964 --> 15:32.499
Sister washed her hands
of him years ago.

15:32.565 --> 15:34.334
And how the hell would
she know he was here?

15:34.401 --> 15:36.069
- Called her?
- He didn't call anybody.

15:36.136 --> 15:37.537
He's a black-out drunk.

15:37.604 --> 15:40.073
He washes up on you again,
I want to be notified.

15:40.140 --> 15:41.208
It's in the computer,
detective.

15:41.274 --> 15:43.476
Just make sure it happens.

15:47.547 --> 15:49.216
Yes?

15:49.282 --> 15:51.551
Mayor Ramos here to see you.

15:51.618 --> 15:53.186
Send him in.

15:59.392 --> 16:01.894
- Irv.
- Mr. Mayor.

16:01.961 --> 16:03.696
Jen.

16:03.763 --> 16:06.166
This is a surprise.
I would have come to you.

16:06.233 --> 16:09.536
Doing my victory lap.
You're my first stop.

16:10.770 --> 16:11.804
Please have a seat.

16:11.871 --> 16:13.640
And congratulations.

16:13.706 --> 16:14.907
Thank you.

16:14.974 --> 16:16.176
It was a great night.

16:16.243 --> 16:18.145
Get you anything?
Water? Coffee?

16:18.211 --> 16:19.912
No. We're good.

16:19.979 --> 16:21.614
Thank you, Ida.

16:23.550 --> 16:26.419
I wanted to thank you
in person for your support.

16:27.487 --> 16:29.622
I doubt it made
much of a difference.

16:29.689 --> 16:30.990
Numbers say otherwise.

16:31.058 --> 16:32.759
You're a popular dude,
Chief--

16:32.825 --> 16:34.327
south of I-10,
east of the river,

16:34.394 --> 16:35.728
Westside,
even the Valley.

16:35.795 --> 16:38.465
The Valley?
Imagine that.

16:39.532 --> 16:41.168
So we're grateful.

16:41.234 --> 16:45.172
You know, you could use
the Chief's office.

16:45.238 --> 16:46.973
It's nicer than mine.

16:47.040 --> 16:48.575
I'm happy here.

16:48.641 --> 16:52.112
Besides, I wouldn't want
to send the wrong message.

16:53.146 --> 16:55.515
We know you've had
other offers.

16:58.218 --> 16:59.519
I haven't accepted any.

16:59.586 --> 17:01.321
Good to hear.

17:01.388 --> 17:03.656
I still intend to step down
at the end of the year.

17:03.723 --> 17:07.427
Then we have till then
to change your mind.

17:15.468 --> 17:17.504
Detective,
you testified previously

17:17.570 --> 17:20.140
that, when you encountered
Mrs. Allen in the church,

17:20.207 --> 17:21.308
she was distraught.

17:21.374 --> 17:22.642
She seemed to be, yes.

17:22.709 --> 17:25.078
There was blood
on her right hand.

17:25.145 --> 17:26.546
There was blood on her dress.

17:26.613 --> 17:29.082
And upon entering
Father Tabakian's office,

17:29.149 --> 17:30.217
what did you see?

17:30.283 --> 17:32.018
He was lying on the floor.

17:32.085 --> 17:33.920
The back of his head
had been bashed in.

17:33.986 --> 17:35.822
He was unresponsive,
not breathing.

17:35.888 --> 17:40.427
A heavy trophy was lying
nearby, covered in blood,

17:40.493 --> 17:42.262
and a pair of scissors
had been placed

17:42.329 --> 17:43.530
under his left hand.

17:43.596 --> 17:46.366
- Placed?
- That was my impression.

17:46.433 --> 17:47.867
Placed?

17:47.934 --> 17:49.236
By whom, in your opinion?

17:49.302 --> 17:51.037
The defendant.
Mrs. Allen.

17:51.104 --> 17:52.639
You didn't
witness her do that.

17:52.705 --> 17:53.740
No.

17:53.806 --> 17:55.508
Were her fingerprints
on the scissors?

17:55.575 --> 17:56.609
No.

17:56.676 --> 17:57.944
Were any prints found
on the scissors?

17:58.010 --> 17:59.346
Father Tabakian's.

17:59.412 --> 18:01.581
What was your initial
assessment at the scene?

18:01.648 --> 18:03.883
That they had quarreled
over the money,

18:03.950 --> 18:06.719
that Mrs. Allen had
struck Father Tabakian
with the trophy,

18:06.786 --> 18:09.322
and then planted
the scissors in his hand

18:09.389 --> 18:11.658
to make it look
like self-defense.

18:11.724 --> 18:13.193
Detective,
your partner testified

18:13.260 --> 18:15.094
that you told him
from the beginning

18:15.162 --> 18:16.296
you believed the scissors
were planted.

18:16.363 --> 18:17.797
- That is correct.
- You never considered

18:17.864 --> 18:19.366
that her story of
self-defense might be true?

18:19.432 --> 18:21.201
Considered and dismissed.

18:23.270 --> 18:26.206
Detective, weren't you
a defendant in a civil suit

18:26.273 --> 18:28.007
where you were accused
of planting evidence?

18:28.074 --> 18:29.309
Yes.

18:29.376 --> 18:30.943
What was the outcome
of that lawsuit?

18:31.010 --> 18:32.479
The jury found
for the plaintiff.

18:34.914 --> 18:36.416
Nothing further.

18:38.685 --> 18:42.121
Detective, did the jury
in that case conclude

18:42.189 --> 18:43.790
that you had planted evidence?

18:43.856 --> 18:46.092
- No.
- Did the findings against you

18:46.159 --> 18:48.528
involve falsifying
of evidence in any way?

18:48.595 --> 18:49.962
No.

18:50.029 --> 18:51.298
And the total amount
in damages

18:51.364 --> 18:52.632
awarded to the plaintiff?

18:52.699 --> 18:53.766
One dollar.

18:53.833 --> 18:55.335
One dollar.

18:55.402 --> 18:57.970
Nothing further, Your Honor.

18:58.037 --> 18:59.872
The witness may step down.

19:04.677 --> 19:07.380
Ms. Chandler,
any other witnesses?

19:07.447 --> 19:08.681
Uh, just one, Your Honor.

19:08.748 --> 19:11.418
The defense calls
Mrs. Anthony Allen.

19:11.484 --> 19:14.554
Uh, Your Honor,
given the late hour,

19:14.621 --> 19:16.623
I suggest we recess
for the day.

19:16.689 --> 19:18.225
Court will resume
in the morning

19:18.291 --> 19:19.726
with Mrs. Allen's testimony.

19:28.000 --> 19:29.369
Señor Bosch.

19:29.436 --> 19:30.503
Gracias, Gladys.

19:30.570 --> 19:31.804
De nada.

19:35.174 --> 19:36.743
- Gracias.
- De nada.

19:52.392 --> 19:54.126
Talk to your mom lately?

19:54.193 --> 19:55.362
We Skyped Sunday.

19:55.428 --> 19:56.896
You should make that
a standing date--

19:56.963 --> 19:58.931
once a week, Sunday.

19:58.998 --> 20:01.067
Well, her Sunday
or my Sunday?

20:01.133 --> 20:02.569
Whichever.

20:02.635 --> 20:04.337
The time difference.
It's so hard.

20:04.404 --> 20:05.938
Plus, she and Reggie
work nights.

20:06.005 --> 20:08.074
It's morning here,
it's evening in Hong Kong,

20:08.140 --> 20:09.175
and it's not even
the same day.

20:09.242 --> 20:11.311
Okay. Don't whine.
Just try.

20:11.378 --> 20:12.712
I'm not whining.

20:12.779 --> 20:14.247
Okay.

20:16.716 --> 20:19.085
You've been working
late a lot.

20:19.151 --> 20:20.720
Prepping the Holland trial.

20:22.188 --> 20:24.657
What? What's that look?

20:24.724 --> 20:26.726
Nothing.

20:26.793 --> 20:28.628
You've been spending
a lot of time with her.

20:28.695 --> 20:31.030
Her? Who? Anita?

20:31.097 --> 20:33.065
Oh, that's what you
call her? Anita?

20:33.132 --> 20:35.268
Deputy DA Benitez to you.

20:35.335 --> 20:36.703
Whatever.

20:38.004 --> 20:39.739
When's the trial?

20:39.806 --> 20:40.940
A few weeks.

20:41.007 --> 20:42.675
I've got court
in the morning,

20:42.742 --> 20:44.444
then tomorrow we go
over to his house,

