of salt-and-pepper
shakedown artists

34:49.755 --> 34:50.989
preying on lonely widows.

34:51.056 --> 34:52.824
- Shake this.
- Eh.

34:52.891 --> 34:54.460
Well, we're disappointed.

34:54.526 --> 34:56.862
But this office will study
the events of this trial

34:56.928 --> 34:59.531
before we decide whether
to retry Mrs. Allen.

34:59.598 --> 35:03.235
Whether to retry?
Are you kidding me?

35:03.302 --> 35:05.237
That chickenshit.

35:06.505 --> 35:07.773
Excuse me.

35:20.051 --> 35:22.688
Mr. District Attorney.
Benitez.

35:22.754 --> 35:23.689
Bosch.

35:23.755 --> 35:25.391
Anita was just
bringing me up to speed

35:25.457 --> 35:26.858
on the Holland case--

35:28.894 --> 35:31.297
All right,
I have to tell you.

35:31.363 --> 35:33.432
After what happened
today, I'm concerned.

35:33.499 --> 35:34.366
Don't be.

35:34.433 --> 35:35.701
And since
you brought it up,

35:35.767 --> 35:36.502
The Allen case,

35:36.568 --> 35:38.103
which way
are you leaning?

35:38.170 --> 35:40.071
- Oh, I've made up my mind.
- Mm-hmm.

35:40.138 --> 35:42.241
This office
will not file new charges

35:42.308 --> 35:43.642
against Veronica Allen.

35:43.709 --> 35:45.143
Hold on a minute.
You're shitting me.

35:45.211 --> 35:46.345
Honey Chandler has painted

35:46.412 --> 35:48.380
an indelible portrait
of you, detective,

35:48.447 --> 35:50.449
one that cannot be erased:

35:50.516 --> 35:52.551
that you can't be trusted,

35:52.618 --> 35:54.253
That you'll do anything,
say anything,

35:54.320 --> 35:55.521
cut any corner, to win.

35:55.587 --> 35:57.022
That's bullshit.
I don't do that.

35:57.088 --> 35:58.757
You have that reputation,
detective,

35:58.824 --> 36:00.359
deserved or not.

36:00.426 --> 36:02.761
Between you and Mrs. Allen
and credibility,

36:02.828 --> 36:04.263
it's no contest.

36:04.330 --> 36:05.731
So, no. I won't refile.

36:05.797 --> 36:07.433
Now if you'll excuse us,
we've got business.

36:07.499 --> 36:09.268
Now, you listen to me,
you smug son of a bitch.

36:09.335 --> 36:10.936
You don't want to pursue this.

36:11.002 --> 36:12.771
You don't want to do your job.

36:12.838 --> 36:15.874
This is payback. This is
your vendetta with Irving.

36:15.941 --> 36:17.576
Harry--

36:17.643 --> 36:19.878
Harry, stop.

36:49.775 --> 36:51.076
Shit.

36:51.142 --> 36:52.511
Dad?

36:52.578 --> 36:53.345
Yeah.

36:53.412 --> 36:55.213
You going to bed?

36:55.281 --> 36:58.016
Yeah.

36:58.083 --> 36:59.718
You finish your homework?

37:02.588 --> 37:04.155
Dad, you're
on the internet.

37:04.222 --> 37:06.258
I'm just doing
something for work.

37:06.325 --> 37:08.494
No, I mean you.

37:08.560 --> 37:10.061
You're on the internet.

37:10.128 --> 37:11.563
You don't want
to pursue this.

37:11.630 --> 37:13.198
You don't want
to do your job.

37:13.265 --> 37:16.335
This is payback. This is
your vendetta with Irving.

37:16.402 --> 37:18.470
Harry. Harry, stop.

37:22.741 --> 37:25.377
You look like you
wanted to kill him.

37:26.778 --> 37:27.746
We had an argument.

37:27.813 --> 37:29.881
I shouldn't
have lost my temper.

37:31.149 --> 37:32.318
Okay?

37:32.384 --> 37:34.019
Well, you're lucky.

37:34.085 --> 37:36.722
It only got,
like, 37 retweets.

37:38.490 --> 37:41.293
You have to be really
careful these days, Dad.

37:41.360 --> 37:43.395
Literally
everything is on camera.

37:43.462 --> 37:45.163
Ain't it the truth.

37:45.230 --> 37:47.666
Okay, honey.
Good night.

37:47.733 --> 37:48.734
Good night.

37:59.711 --> 38:00.879
Ah, shit.

38:04.115 --> 38:05.551
50 bucks.

38:07.753 --> 38:08.787
Deal.

38:08.854 --> 38:09.988
Get in.

38:25.537 --> 38:28.206
This class of recruits

38:28.273 --> 38:30.376
exemplifies the core values

38:30.442 --> 38:32.611
of the Los Angeles
Police Department:

38:34.245 --> 38:36.648
service to the community,

38:36.715 --> 38:39.050
reverence for the law,

38:39.117 --> 38:43.088
integrity. leadership,

38:43.154 --> 38:45.090
respect for all people.

38:47.393 --> 38:50.128
Keep these values in mind,

38:50.195 --> 38:53.098
and strive to uphold them
throughout your careers.

38:56.802 --> 39:00.005
It is a privilege to be
a Los Angeles police officer.

39:01.607 --> 39:05.010
It is an honor
to wear this uniform.

39:06.878 --> 39:12.484
And with it comes
enormous responsibility

39:12.551 --> 39:13.819
and an awesome commitment

39:13.885 --> 39:16.788
to protect this city
and its citizens...

39:19.791 --> 39:21.893
with your lives if necessary.

39:23.395 --> 39:25.330
Not so many years ago,

39:25.397 --> 39:27.499
on a day like this...

39:29.735 --> 39:31.603
I was in the audience.

39:37.776 --> 39:40.111
My son graduated that day.

39:41.747 --> 39:43.682
And I could not
have been prouder.

39:47.519 --> 39:50.956
My son honored
that commitment.

39:52.190 --> 39:54.726
He made the ultimate
sacrifice.

39:56.394 --> 40:00.899
So I honor his memory every
time I put on this uniform,

40:00.966 --> 40:05.170
just as you honor
the memory of every officer

40:05.236 --> 40:08.474
who has given his or her life
in the line of duty.

40:09.675 --> 40:11.643
Wear it with pride.

40:12.844 --> 40:15.447
Respect what it represents:

40:17.015 --> 40:20.452
to serve and protect
the citizens of Los Angeles.

40:20.519 --> 40:23.188
Class 516.

40:23.254 --> 40:25.423
A-ten-hut!

40:26.625 --> 40:29.661
Class 516,

40:29.728 --> 40:33.599
on behalf of the Mayor
and the City of Los Angeles,

40:33.665 --> 40:36.902
welcome to the Los Angeles
Police Department.

40:57.222 --> 40:59.758
Smile, man, smile.

41:01.493 --> 41:03.495
A happy day.
Well done, Irv.

41:03.562 --> 41:05.631
Thank you, Brad.

41:05.697 --> 41:07.465
How goes the search?

41:07.533 --> 41:08.834
The board's split.

41:08.900 --> 41:10.936
Do we pick an
insider like you?

41:11.002 --> 41:12.003
Go outside,

41:12.070 --> 41:13.805
someone with no ties
to the department?

41:13.872 --> 41:15.306
No potential
conflicts of interest?

41:15.373 --> 41:18.143
Maybe it's time for
the first female chief,

41:18.209 --> 41:19.878
the first Latino.

41:19.945 --> 41:21.880
You could
make it easy on us.

41:21.947 --> 41:23.114
Stick around.

41:23.181 --> 41:24.950
Put us out of our misery.

41:25.016 --> 41:27.185
Look, I've already
told the mayor.

41:27.252 --> 41:30.856
I know, I know. You're
a stubborn son of a bitch.

41:32.057 --> 41:33.124
So I hear.

41:33.191 --> 41:34.359
Talk him into it?

41:34.425 --> 41:35.994
What do you think,
Hector?

41:36.061 --> 41:39.364
That was moving, Irv,
inspirational,

41:39.430 --> 41:40.999
first-rate. I mean it.

41:41.066 --> 41:43.034
You're held in high regard
by your troops.

41:43.101 --> 41:45.303
- Thank you.
- Mr. Mayor.

41:45.370 --> 41:48.339
- Bradley.
- Richard.

41:48.406 --> 41:51.342
Congratulations, Chief.

41:51.409 --> 41:53.545
Um, a word?

41:54.980 --> 41:56.147
Gentlemen.

42:02.754 --> 42:06.992
You need to put your attack
dog back on his leash.

42:18.937 --> 42:21.106
Come in.

42:21.172 --> 42:22.440
Captain?

42:22.507 --> 42:25.343
I just had a call
from Chief Irving.

42:25.410 --> 42:27.412
It's about Bosch.

42:27.478 --> 42:28.980
I have something
to show you.

42:32.984 --> 42:35.220
I thought he was
more chipper lately,

42:35.286 --> 42:37.989
- more hopeful.
- Probably just high.

42:38.056 --> 42:40.425
Mr. Meadows, was
your son in treatment?

42:40.491 --> 42:42.894
NA? AA?

42:42.961 --> 42:44.362
Any veteran's groups?

42:44.429 --> 42:45.697
He'd tell you he was.

42:45.764 --> 42:48.533
When he first got back he was.

42:48.600 --> 42:50.068
Did he have a cell phone?

42:50.135 --> 42:53.171
One after another.
What do they call them?

42:53.238 --> 42:54.505
Burners.

42:54.572 --> 42:56.474
Yeah, always
a different number.

42:56.541 --> 42:58.343
If we can get a hold
of the latest.

42:58.409 --> 43:00.378
We're like to talk to anyone
who might have seen him

43:00.445 --> 43:02.480
or spoken to him recently.

43:02.547 --> 43:04.582
Friends, girlfriends.

43:04.650 --> 43:06.918
Ohh.
None that we knew of.

43:06.985 --> 43:11.089
Army buds? Anybody he might
have kept in touch with?

43:12.190 --> 43:13.692
I think he pretty much

43:13.759 --> 43:15.727
lost touch with everyone.

43:15.794 --> 43:17.896
Did you see him often?

43:19.130 --> 43:20.298
First of the month.

43:20.365 --> 43:21.900
Pick up his check.

43:23.068 --> 43:24.770
That was the deal.
I'd cash it for him,

43:24.836 --> 43:26.171
and that was that.

43:26.237 --> 43:28.940
No. Not just.

43:29.007 --> 43:32.610
A meal, a change of clothes,

43:32.678 --> 43:34.713
hot shower.

43:34.780 --> 43:37.082
I'd do his wash for him.

43:38.316 --> 43:40.686
Some men never grow up.

43:42.387 --> 43:44.189
You ever visit him?

43:44.255 --> 43:46.391
He wouldn't ever tell us
where he was living.

43:46.457 --> 43:49.327
He was ashamed, Hal.

44:05.310 --> 44:08.646
That was just before he
deployed the first time.

44:08.714 --> 44:10.581
The first time?

44:10.648 --> 44:14.352
Once to Iraq,
twice to Afghanistan.

44:14.419 --> 44:16.121
A Green Beret.

44:16.187 --> 44:19.190
That's a real accomplishment,
Mrs. Meadows.

44:20.491 --> 44:21.893
We were proud of him.

44:21.960 --> 44:23.494
I'm sure you are.

44:23.561 --> 44:27.332
It wrecked him,
this damn war.

44:27.398 --> 44:31.036
He had no end of troubles
when he finally came home.

44:32.704 --> 44:35.273
Now this.

44:35.340 --> 44:37.142
Take your time.

44:55.560 --> 44:57.996
I'll tell you
what isn't here:

44:58.063 --> 44:59.530
his kit.

44:59.597 --> 45:01.599
Anything to do
with his service.

45:01.666 --> 45:04.169
No unit patches,
no challenge coins,

45:04.235 --> 45:08.439
no souvenirs,
no uniform, no beret.

45:08.506 --> 45:10.175
Just this one picture.

45:11.209 --> 45:13.845
He kept his things at The Bin.

45:13.912 --> 45:15.881
Downtown?
On Fifth Street?

45:15.947 --> 45:18.549
Yeah, his important
things from the army.

45:18.616 --> 45:20.418
The RV wasn't safe.

45:20.485 --> 45:22.053
Why didn't he
keep them here?

45:23.889 --> 45:26.491
He said he didn't
want to infect us.

45:29.160 --> 45:30.395
Thank you.

45:35.533 --> 45:37.302
I'll write the warrant.

45:40.605 --> 45:41.773
- Hey.
- Oh.

45:41.840 --> 45:43.274
Sorry I'm late.

45:43.341 --> 45:46.377
Traffic coming from
the Westside was murder,

45:46.444 --> 45:47.545
miserable.

45:47.612 --> 45:48.679
We made ramen.

45:48.746 --> 45:50.581
- I see that.
- Want some?

45:50.648 --> 45:52.851
It's good. Salty. Slurpy.

45:52.918 --> 45:54.185
Naw, I'm not hungry,

45:54.252 --> 45:55.854
but I'm gonna grab a beer
and come join you.

46:01.192 --> 46:02.994
So, Grace,

46:03.061 --> 46:04.529
what brings you by?

46:04.595 --> 46:07.565
Mm, just checking
on you two,

46:07.632 --> 46:09.334
making sure you're
getting along.

46:09.400 --> 46:11.302
- We're doing good. Maddie?
- Excellent.

46:11.369 --> 46:12.770
Harry's gonna teach me
how to drive.

46:12.838 --> 46:14.172
Ooh. Brave man.

46:14.239 --> 46:15.073
We'll see.

46:15.140 --> 46:16.307
Maddie was just telling me

46:16.374 --> 46:17.843
about Eleanor and Reggie
in Hong Kong.

46:17.909 --> 46:19.544
Doing well,
by all accounts.

46:19.610 --> 46:21.012
Yeah,
but you must miss them.

46:21.079 --> 46:23.681
A lot. They're planning
to come home for Christmas.

46:23.748 --> 46:26.184
They are?
Good to know.

46:26.251 --> 46:28.019
Grace, seconds?

46:28.086 --> 46:29.787
No, I'm good, thanks.
It was delish.

46:29.855 --> 46:31.122
Thanks.

46:36.527 --> 46:37.528
I have homework.

46:37.595 --> 46:38.763
Okay.

46:38.830 --> 46:40.098
It's good to see you,
Maddie.

46:40.165 --> 46:41.799
You, too.
Tell Lisa I said hi.

46:41.867 --> 46:43.101
Will do.

46:52.944 --> 46:55.480
Your little outburst
with the DA.

46:55.546 --> 46:57.348
It's gone viral.

46:57.415 --> 47:00.351
IA is going to file
a 128 against you.

47:00.418 --> 47:01.719
What a pain in the ass.

47:01.786 --> 47:03.221
Do me a favor,
take their call.

47:03.288 --> 47:04.289
Yeah, yeah.

47:05.390 --> 47:06.524
No, I mean it.

47:06.591 --> 47:08.259
Lewis is
on the war path.

47:08.326 --> 47:09.427
I said yeah.

47:13.764 --> 47:15.033
I'm worried
about you, Harry.

47:15.100 --> 47:16.001
Don't be. I'm fine.

47:16.067 --> 47:17.302
I don't think you are.

47:17.368 --> 47:18.503
I'm tired is all.

47:18.569 --> 47:19.737
I'm not sleeping.

47:19.804 --> 47:21.973
All right, well,
take some vacation days.

47:22.040 --> 47:23.374
When Maddie
finishes school.

47:31.216 --> 47:33.251
You know what?
Fuck this.

47:33.318 --> 47:36.054
This is me, Grace, asking.

47:36.121 --> 47:38.423
What the fuck
is eating you, Harry?

47:39.590 --> 47:41.226
I thought that closing
your mother's murder

47:41.292 --> 47:42.827
would bring you some peace.

47:42.894 --> 47:44.362
Instead, it's made you
more miserable.

47:44.429 --> 47:45.730
Peace?

47:45.796 --> 47:47.698
That's a load of shit.

47:47.765 --> 47:49.300
Her murderer
got away with it,

47:49.367 --> 47:51.469
and my department
helped him do it.

47:51.536 --> 47:52.603
Things have changed.

47:52.670 --> 47:53.838
It's not the same
department.

47:53.905 --> 47:55.073
It's the same world.

47:55.140 --> 47:58.743
You need to get over it

47:58.809 --> 48:01.312
and get yourself right.

48:26.671 --> 48:28.039
Just wanted
to say good night.

48:29.674 --> 48:31.142
Good night, honey.

48:33.911 --> 48:34.980
You okay?

48:35.046 --> 48:36.481
Yeah, I'm fine.

48:38.316 --> 48:40.818
What did Grace want,
really?

48:40.885 --> 48:43.621
Just wanted
to make sure we're okay.

48:45.056 --> 48:46.024
We are, right?

48:46.091 --> 48:48.326
Of course. Absolutely.

48:48.393 --> 48:49.694
Good.

48:53.498 --> 48:54.865
- Good night.
- Good night.

48:54.932 --> 48:56.567
- Love you.
- Love you, too.

49:26.331 --> 49:27.432
Aah!

49:27.498 --> 49:28.633
No!

50:38.636 --> 50:40.405
Who the fuck are you?
